Variation. The snout can be subacuminate or rounded in lateral view, and in some individuals nostrils are not over an elevation. The digital webbing formula presents variation (
Tab. 1
). Some pustules can be observed in the dorsum, flanks, and legs of some individuals. These pustules were probably caused by some parasite we could not identify. Color of dorsum may be olive. Variations in measurements are given in table 2 .
